                      </tr>
                  </table></td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td height="15"></td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="5">
                      <tr>
                        <td width="2%"><img src="images/bull.jpg" width="6" height="6" /></td>
                        <td width="98%" align="left"><strong class="text"> TEAM OF OFFICE : </strong></td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                        <td>&nbsp;</td>
                        <td align="left" class="text">The term of office of the managing Committee shall be for  the period of three years commencing from the date of their election. Provided  that any such Managing Committee member shall notwithstanding the expiry of the  said period of three years, continue to hold office until fresh nomination or  election are held and Managing Committee declared as formed.</td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                        <td height="15"></td>
                        <td height="15" align="left"></td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                        <td><img src="images/bull.jpg" width="6" height="6" /></td>
                        <td align="left"><strong class="text">THE FUNCTION OF THE MANAGING COMMITTEE</strong></td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                        <td>&nbsp;</td>
                        <td align="left"><ol>
                            <li class="text">To  assist the Association in overall function administration , finance and all  such matters which are incidental, ancillary ,subsidiary and conducive for promotion  and propagation of the Association.</li>
                          <li class="text">The Managing Committee can create, establish and  control such other committees for promoting the cause as per the aims and  objects of the Association with the approval of general body or ex-facto  sanction thereafter. </li>
                        </ol></td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                        <td height="15"></td>
                        <td height="15" align="left"></td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                        <td><img src="images/bull.jpg" width="6" height="6" /></td>
                        <td align="left"><strong class="text">POWER OF MANAGING COMMITTEE</strong></td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                        <td>&nbsp;</td>
                        <td align="left"><ol>
                            <ul>
                              <li class="text">The  Managing Committee shall have full powers to carry out the work of the  Association as per aims and object and shall have monthly meeting to be  conducted for sanctioning the monthly expenditure, assessing the income and  suggesting the of cause of the&nbsp;  Association.</li>
                              <li class="text">The  Managing Committee shall present its yearly report and budget for the ensuing  year before the general Body for approval and invite suggestion ,remedies and  objections, if any, and put into effect or react, as the case may be, in  subsequent years.</li>
                              <li class="text">The  Managing Committee shall create as much sub-committees and/or as per requirements  and shall have full powers to deal with.</li>
                              <li class="text">The  Managing Committee shall have full powers to appoint requisite staff for carrying  out the administration of the Association and also have disciplinary powers to  punish, or dismiss the staff so appointed.</li>
                              <li class="text">The  Managing Committee shall have powers to hear the grievances either directly or  through committee if so appointed and/or complaints of the publish and any  Authority and take cognizance of either to take the matter with appropriate  Authority and/or propose /take remedial action to redress the  difficulties/complaints etc.</li>
                              <li class="text">The Managing Committee shall make efforts in  representing wherever necessary, before the appropriate authorities, the  anomalies , inequities and ambiguities in various industrial laws and for  removing administrative hardship to establishment/factories in general and  practitioners in particular.</li>
                              <li><span class="text">The  Managing Committee shall make representation depute delegation to Appropriate  authorities and/or any bodies or institutions, Governments etc. for the common  interest of the members and Association. </span>&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>
                            </ul></td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                        <td height="15"></td>
                        <td height="15" align="left"></td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                        <td><img src="images/bull.jpg" width="6" height="6" /></td>
                        <td align="left" class="text"><strong>MEETINGS</strong></td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                        <td>&nbsp;</td>
                        <td align="left"><span class="text">The Managing Committee may, from time to time, meet to  dispose off all important communication and references and consider all such  matters which may be on the agenda or which may be permitted by the Chairman.  Three-fifth members in person shall be the quorum. </span>
                            <p class="text"> The  General Secretary shall within 15 days of the date of election of the Managing  Committee summon the first meeting of the Managing Committee to transact the  following business: </p>
                          <ol>
                              <li class="text">To read and confirm the minutes of the last meeting.</li>
                            <li class="text"> To elect the office-bearers. </li>
                            <li class="text"> To co-opt the requisite number of members, not exceeding five. </li>
                            <li class="text"> To  appoint any committee or sub- committee. </li>
                            <li class="text"> To report about the taking over of the charge.</li>
                            <li class="text"> To transact such other business as may be deemed fit.</li>
                          </ol>
                          <span class="text">The General Secretary at any time  Chairman of his own motion or upon a request in writing by any three members of  the Managing Committee may summon a meeting of the Managing Committee to  transact any business. Ordinarily the meeting of the Managing Committee shall  be called at least once a month. </span>
                            <p class="text">Notice  of every meeting of the Managing Committee stating the general particulars of  the business to be transacted at the meeting shall be hand delivered or sent by  post to each member of the Managing Committee to his last known address at  least seven days before the meeting but the proceedings of any meeting shall  not be invalidated by any irregularity in respect of such a notice or by an  accidental omission to give such a notice to or non-receipt of such notice by  any member. Urgent meeting may be called by the chairman or the General  Secretary by short notice. </p>
                          <span class="text">The minutes of every meeting of the Managing Committee  shall be kept by anyone of the General Secretary or secretary. Resolutions of  the Managing Committee may also be passed by circulars in case of any  emergency. A circular resolution signed by three-fourths of the members of the  Managing Committee for the time being present in Mumbai, shall in all respects  be as valid and effective as a resolution passed at a meeting of the Managing  Committee duly called and held. The Chairman or the General Secretary shall be  entitled to decide whether any matter should be decided by a circular  resolution.</span></td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                        <td height="15"></td>
                        <td height="15" align="left"></td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                        <td><img src="images/bull.jpg" width="6" height="6" /></td>
                        <td align="left" class="text"><strong>VACANCY OF THE MANAGING COMMITTEE</strong></td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                        <td>&nbsp;</td>
                        <td align="left" class="text">Any member of the Managing Committee shall be  deemed to have vacated his membership on Managing Committee if he absents  himself, without previous intimation, in three consecutive meetings. The  Managing Committee may fill up the vacancy of any of its members or office  bearers or of any member on any Committee or Sub-Committee.</td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                        <td height="15"></td>
                        <td height="15" align="left"></td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                        <td><img src="images/bull.jpg" width="6" height="6" /></td>
                        <td align="left" class="text"><strong>FUNCTIONS OF OFFICE BEARERS</strong></td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                        <td>&nbsp;</td>
                        <td align="left"><span class="text">Following  shall be the usual functions of the respective office Bearers. </span>
                            <ol>
                              <li class="text"><strong>CHAIRMAN:</strong> He  shall preside over, conduct and regulate all meetings and his rulings on any  point of order and decision as to the results of voting shall be final and  conclusive. He shall have an additional casting vote in case of a tie. He shall  have a general supervision over the affairs of the Association. </li>
                              <li class="text"><strong>VICE-CHAIRMAN:</strong> In  the absence of the Chairman, he shall exercise all the powers of the Chairman. </li>
                              <li class="text"><strong>GENERAL  SECRETARY, SECRETARIES &amp; JOINT SECRETARIES : </strong>
                                  <p class="text">(I)  The General Secretary shall be over-all incharge of the Administration &amp;  Management of the Association and shall carry out all such work as is required  to be done by the Managing committee except what is entrusted to the foregoing  office bearers or what may be or in specifically entrusted to any members or  members of the Managing Committee either by the Managing Committee or by the  general body of the Association or under this Constitution. </p>
                                <p class="text">(II)  The Secretaries shall carry out all such work as entrusted by the General Secretary  from time to time. In absence of General Secretary, the Secretaries will assume  the same power and act as General Secretary. </p>
                                <p class="text">(III)  The Joint Secretaries shall carry out all such work as entrusted by the General  Secretary and Secretaries from time to time. In absence of General Secretary  and Secretaries, the Joint Secretaries will assume the same power and act as  General Secretary and Secretary. </p>
                              </li>
                              <li class="text"><strong>TREASURER &amp;  JOINT TREASURER :</strong> He shall ordinarily cause proper maintenance of the books of  accounts, and in association with the General Secretary/ Secretaries, he shall  cause;
                                <ol>
                                    <li>All payments made  to the Association to be received and necessary receipts to be passed;</li>
                                  <li>All expenses of  the Association except major non recurring or capital expenses exceeding Rs. 500/-  to be defrayed. </li>
                                </ol>
                              </li>
                            </ol>
                          <span class="text">Joint Treasurer shall assist Treasurer in all matters  and shall act in absence of Treasurer as regular Treasurer.</span></td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                        <td height="15"></td>
                        <td height="15" align="left"></td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                        <td><img src="images/bull.jpg" width="6" height="6" /></td>
                        <td align="left" class="text"><strong>ACCOUNTS &amp; FUNDS</strong></td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                        <td>&nbsp;</td>
                        <td align="left"><span class="text">Books  of accounts shall be regularly audited by a Charted Accountant qualified under section  226 of Companies Act, 1956 or any statutory modifications or re- inactment  thereof.&nbsp; </span>
                            <p class="text">Funds  and receipt of the Association except petty cash shall be deposited in a banks  in a current, savings or deposit account or accounts opened in the name of  Association, for the purpose as may be decided by the Managing Committee from  time to time. The bank account or accounts shall be operated jointly by any two  of the following office-bearers: </p>
                          <ol>
                              <li class="text">The Chairman.</li>
                            <li class="text">&nbsp;The General Secretary.</li>
                            <li class="text">&nbsp;The Secretaries</li>
                            <li class="text">&nbsp;The Hon. Treasurer. </li>
                          </ol></td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                        <td height="15"></td>
                        <td height="15" align="left"></td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                        <td><img src="images/bull.jpg" width="6" height="6" /></td>
                        <td align="left" class="text"><strong>MINUTES BOOK</strong></td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                        <td>&nbsp;</td>
                        <td align="left" class="text">The  Managing Committee shall cause to be kept regular books in which Minutes of its  own proceedings and those of the general meetings shall be regularly recorded.  Such minutes shall be open for inspection during the usual business hours by  any member of the Association on his giving at least 24 hours notice to the  General Secretary of the Association and such member shall be entitled to take  such extracts therefrom as he may deem fit.</td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                        <td height="15"></td>
                        <td height="15" align="left"></td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                        <td><img src="images/bull.jpg" width="6" height="6" /></td>
                        <td align="left" class="text"><strong>ALTERATION, ADDITION OR ABRIDGEMENT OF OBJECT OR  THE NAME THE ASSOCIATION </strong></td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                        <td>&nbsp;</td>
                        <td align="left" class="text">For the purpose of altering, adding or  abridgening any object or objects, purpose or purposes, or altering name of the  Association the procedure laid down under relevant Act under which the  association is registered shall be followed.</td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                        <td height="15"></td>
                        <td height="15" align="left"></td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                        <td><img src="images/bull.jpg" width="6" height="6" /></td>
                        <td align="left" class="text"><strong>ALTERATION IN ARTICLES</strong></td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                        <td>&nbsp;</td>
                        <td align="left" class="text">Subject  to above Article 31, no amendments, alterations, additions or omission in this  Constitution, or repeal thereof, shall be effected except by a resolution of  the Member of the Association at any general meeting by a majority of the total  members present in person and entitle to vote, provided the proposed  amendments, etc. are duly circulated amongst the members along with the notice  convening the general meeting. </td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                        <td height="15"></td>
                        <td height="15" align="left"></td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                        <td><img src="images/bull.jpg" width="6" height="6" /></td>
                        <td align="left" class="text"><strong>DISSOLUTION</strong></td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                        <td>&nbsp;</td>
                        <td align="left" class="text">The Association may dissolve itself according to  the procedure laid down under Section 13 &amp; 14 of Societies Registration  Act, 1860, as amended from time to time, except the provision of Voting by  Proxy.</td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                        <td height="15"></td>
                        <td height="15" align="left"></td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                        <td><img src="images/bull.jpg" width="6" height="6" /></td>
                        <td align="left" class="text"><strong>REPEAL</strong></td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                        <td>&nbsp;</td>
                        <td align="left" class="text">Constitution of the Association as adopted by  the members of the Association at their meeting held on 25-2-95 and as amended  from time to time till that date, is hereby repealed except to the extent and  for the purpose mentioned at relevant cause.</td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                        <td height="15"></td>
                        <td height="15" align="left"></td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                        <td><img src="images/bull.jpg" width="6" height="6" /></td>
                        <td align="left" class="text"><strong>SAVINGS</strong></td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                        <td>&nbsp;</td>
                        <td align="left"><ol>
                            <li class="text">Notwithstanding the repeal of the constitution referred to in Article 34,  members already enrolled as Founder/ Member on the day on which this  constitution comes into force shall be deemed to have been duly enrolled as  such members under this constitution.</li>
                          <li class="text">The election of  members of the Managing Committee made under the Constitution repealed under  Article 34 above shall be deemed to be duly made under Article 22 of the  constitution, subject to the approval of the General Body convened to adopt  this Constitution. Provided that, if any vacancy of any member of office  bearers is caused on account of want of approval of the aforesaid general  meeting, it shall be filled up by the Managing Committee.</li>
                          <li class="text">The repeal of the  constitution referred to in Article 34 shall not affect anything done or any  actions or decisions taken or deemed to have been taken under and in pursuance  of any provisions of the said Constitution and the same shall have effect under  this Constitution also unless otherwise provided hereinbefore or unless  contrary is decided upon or done.</li>
                          <li class="text">If any difficulty arises is giving effect to the  provisions of the Article of the Constitution or as to its interpretation or  implementation, the decision of the Managing Committee shall be final.</li>
                        </ol></td>
                      </tr>
                  </table></td>
                </tr>
